<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1362145" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/SCHOOL-CLOSED.jpg?resize=600%2C337&#038;ssl=1" alt="Coronavirus: School reopens in South Africa despite virus surge" width="600" height="337" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/SCHOOL-CLOSED.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/SCHOOL-CLOSED.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/SCHOOL-CLOSED.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/SCHOOL-CLOSED.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/SCHOOL-CLOSED.jpg?resize=200%2C112&amp;ssl=1 200w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> South Africa’s education ministry has continued with its phased reopening of schools despite the surge in Coronavirus cases. Grades R (five-year-olds), Grade six (11-year-olds), and Grade 11 (16-year-olds) are returning to school on Monday, a month after final year students reopened. There have been coronavirus infections among learners and teachers since the resumption of classes in June. The Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga said school administrators should continue following health guidelines.’ She said 2,740 teachers and 1,260 learners had been infected with coronavirus since final year students resumed classes last month. Some 11 teachers and three learners succumbed to the virus. Some parents, learners, and teachers have been calling for the closure of schools citing the rising number of coronavirus cases. The country has been reporting thousands of new cases every day, with the total number currently at 196,750 including 3,199 deaths. BBC Vanguard More than 200 pupils and staff who returned to a boarding school in South Africa's Eastern Cape province this month tested positive for coronavirus (COVID-19) on Tuesday, officials said. Eastern Cape accounts for around 15 percent of South Africa's 101,590 COVID-19 cases, making it the country's third worst affected province.… June 24, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" An hour before the gates opened, dozens of uniformed students wearing face masks stood silently in single file outside their schools in the dusty South African township of Tembisa. "Have you seen how many are waiting to come in?" said Eddie Kekana, the headmaster of Winnie Mandela Secondary School, just… June 8, 2020 In "Foreign" Chinese youngsters in the global virus epicentre of Wuhan filed back to class on Wednesday, wearing masks and walking in single file past thermal scanners. Senior school students in 121 institutions were back in front of chalkboards and digital displays for the first time since their city -- the ground… May 6, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates"